---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="What to Wear for a Passport Photo: Complete Dress Code Guide 2025"
  description="Can you wear glasses, makeup, or a tank top in your passport photo? Complete passport photo dress code guide covering clothing rules, colors, and what's not allowed."
>
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 mt-[80px] md:mt-10">

    <!-- Breadcrumbs -->
    <nav class="mb-8">
      <ol class="flex items-center space-x-2 text-sm text-gray-600">
        <li><a href="/" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">Home</a></li>
        <li><span class="text-gray-400">/</span></li>
        <li><a href="/blogs" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">Blog</a></li>
        <li><span class="text-gray-400">/</span></li>
        <li class="text-gray-900">Passport Photo Dress Code</li>
      </ol>
    </nav>

    <!-- Category Badge -->
    <div class="mb-6">
      <span class="px-4 py-2 bg-primary text-white text-sm font-crimson font-medium rounded-full">
        Guides
      </span>
    </div>

    <!-- Title -->
    <h1 class="font-crimson text-[40px] md:text-[60px] leading-tight text-gray-900 mb-6">
      What to Wear for a Passport Photo: Complete Dress Code Guide
    </h1>

    <!-- Meta -->
    <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-4 text-gray-600 mb-8 pb-8 border-b-2 border-gray-200">
      <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
        <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 7V3m8 4V3m-9 8h10M5 21h14a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v12a2 2 0 002 2z"></path>
        </svg>
        <span>February 25, 2026</span>
      </div>
      <span class="text-gray-400">•</span>
      <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
        <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 8v4l3 3m6-3a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
        </svg>
        <span>9 min read</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Featured Image -->
    <div class="mb-12 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden">
      <img
        src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1521791136064-7986c2920216?w=1200&h=600&fit=crop"
        alt="What to wear for a passport photo — passport dress code guide"
        class="w-full h-auto"
        width="1200"
        height="600"
        loading="eager"
      />
    </div>

    <!-- Article Content -->
    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

      <!-- Intro -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-tertiary to-green-50 border-2 border-secondary/30 rounded-2xl p-8 mb-8">
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-0">
          A rejected passport photo can delay your travel plans by weeks. The US Department of State and passport authorities worldwide have strict rules on what you can and cannot wear. This guide answers the most common questions — from glasses and makeup to tank tops and turtlenecks — so your photo gets accepted the first time.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Quick Answer Box -->
      <div class="bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
        <h2 class="font-crimson text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Quick Answer: Passport Photo Dress Rules</h2>
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-crimson text-lg text-green-700 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2"><span>✅</span> Allowed</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-500 font-bold">✓</span> Everyday clothing (t-shirts, blouses, shirts)</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-500 font-bold">✓</span> Natural makeup</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-500 font-bold">✓</span> Tank tops and sleeveless tops</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-500 font-bold">✓</span> Turtlenecks and high-neck tops</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-500 font-bold">✓</span> Earrings and small jewelry</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-500 font-bold">✓</span> Religious head coverings (with approval)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-crimson text-lg text-red-700 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2"><span>❌</span> Not Allowed</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-500 font-bold">✗</span> Glasses (as of 2016 US rules)</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-500 font-bold">✗</span> Uniforms or camouflage</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-500 font-bold">✗</span> Hats (unless religious)</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-500 font-bold">✗</span> Heavily altered appearance makeup</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-500 font-bold">✗</span> Headphones or wireless earpieces</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-500 font-bold">✗</span> White clothing (blends with background)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="font-crimson text-[30px] md:text-[40px] text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">Can You Wear Glasses in a Passport Photo?</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        <strong>No.</strong> Since November 2016, the US Department of State no longer accepts passport photos with glasses — even prescription glasses without tints. This rule aligns with ICAO (International Civil Aviation Organization) biometric standards used by most countries worldwide.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-amber-50 border-2 border-amber-200 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6">
        <div class="flex items-start space-x-3">
          <span class="text-amber-500 text-2xl">⚠️</span>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-crimson text-lg font-medium text-amber-900 mb-2">Exception</h4>
            <p class="text-amber-800 text-sm">
              If you cannot remove your glasses for medical reasons and have a signed statement from a medical professional, you may request an exception. Contact your passport acceptance facility before your appointment.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Many countries including the UK, Canada, Australia, and India also follow the no-glasses rule. Always remove glasses before taking your passport photo to avoid automatic rejection.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-crimson text-[30px] md:text-[40px] text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">Can You Wear Makeup for a Passport Photo?</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        <strong>Yes</strong> — natural, everyday makeup is perfectly fine. The key rule is that your photo must represent your normal appearance so you're recognizable when you travel. Subtle makeup like foundation, blush, mascara, and natural lip color is fully acceptable.
      </p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
        <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-200 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-crimson text-xl text-gray-900 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">✅ Makeup That's Fine</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
            <li>• Foundation &amp; concealer</li>
            <li>• Natural blush &amp; bronzer</li>
            <li>• Mascara and eyeliner</li>
            <li>• Natural-shade lipstick</li>
            <li>• Setting powder</li>
            <li>• Eyebrow makeup</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-200 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-crimson text-xl text-gray-900 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">❌ Makeup to Avoid</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
            <li>• Stage or theatrical makeup</li>
            <li>• Face paint or body art</li>
            <li>• Very dark or heavy contouring</li>
            <li>• Glitter or shimmer products</li>
            <li>• Anything that alters your facial structure</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="font-crimson text-[30px] md:text-[40px] text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">Can You Wear a Tank Top in Your Passport Photo?</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        <strong>Yes.</strong> Tank tops and sleeveless clothing are permitted in US passport photos. The rules only restrict specific items (uniforms, hats, glasses) — everyday clothing choices including tank tops, t-shirts, blouses, and even formal wear are all acceptable.
      </p>

      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        The only clothing-related restriction is that your clothing should contrast with the white background. This means <strong>avoid wearing white or very light-colored tops</strong> that could blend into the background.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 border-2 border-blue-200 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
        <div class="flex items-start space-x-3">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600 mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
          </svg>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-crimson text-lg font-medium text-blue-900 mb-2">Best Colors to Wear</h4>
            <p class="text-blue-800 text-sm">
              Medium tones work best: navy, dark blue, grey, burgundy, forest green, or black. Avoid pure white, off-white, and very light pastels. Solid colors are preferred over busy patterns.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="font-crimson text-[30px] md:text-[40px] text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">Can You Wear a Turtleneck in a Passport Photo?</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        <strong>Yes.</strong> Turtlenecks and high-neck tops are completely acceptable for US passport photos. There are no restrictions on neckline choice. Crewnecks, V-necks, turtlenecks, mock-necks — all are fine as long as the top contrasts with the white background.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-crimson text-[30px] md:text-[40px] text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">Can You Wear Earrings in a Passport Photo?</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        <strong>Yes</strong>, earrings are allowed. Small, everyday earrings (studs, small hoops) are perfectly fine. However, very large statement earrings that could obscure your face or that create an unusual silhouette around your head might raise flags during manual review. When in doubt, stick with neutral, small earrings.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-crimson text-[30px] md:text-[40px] text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">Indian Passport Photo Rules — Clothing</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Indian passport photo requirements broadly follow ICAO standards with a few specifics:
      </p>

      <div class="bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden mb-8">
        <table class="w-full">
          <thead class="bg-gradient-to-r from-tertiary to-green-50">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-6 py-4 text-left font-crimson text-lg text-gray-900">Rule</th>
              <th class="px-6 py-4 text-left font-crimson text-lg text-gray-900">Indian Passport</th>
              <th class="px-6 py-4 text-left font-crimson text-lg text-gray-900">US Passport</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-200">
            <tr><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Glasses</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Not allowed</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Not allowed</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Background</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">White only</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">White/off-white</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Uniforms</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Not allowed</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Not allowed</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Religious headwear</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Allowed</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Allowed</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Makeup</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Natural only</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Natural only</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Photo size</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">51×51 mm (2×2")</td><td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">2×2 inches</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 class="font-crimson text-[30px] md:text-[40px] text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">Tips for the Perfect Passport Photo</h2>

      <ol class="space-y-6 mb-8">
        <li class="flex items-start space-x-4">
          <div class="w-8 h-8 bg-gradient-to-br from-primary to-secondary rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <span class="text-white font-crimson font-bold">1</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-crimson text-xl font-medium text-gray-900 mb-2">Wear a medium-toned solid top</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Choose navy, dark blue, grey, or any solid color that contrasts well with the white background. Avoid white, off-white, and bright patterns.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start space-x-4">
          <div class="w-8 h-8 bg-gradient-to-br from-primary to-secondary rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <span class="text-white font-crimson font-bold">2</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-crimson text-xl font-medium text-gray-900 mb-2">Remove glasses before the photo</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Even if you wear glasses every day, remove them for the photo. This is a hard rule in most countries since 2016.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start space-x-4">
          <div class="w-8 h-8 bg-gradient-to-br from-primary to-secondary rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <span class="text-white font-crimson font-bold">3</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-crimson text-xl font-medium text-gray-900 mb-2">Keep makeup natural</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Wear your everyday makeup. Avoid heavy contouring, shimmer, or anything that dramatically changes how your face looks.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start space-x-4">
          <div class="w-8 h-8 bg-gradient-to-br from-primary to-secondary rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <span class="text-white font-crimson font-bold">4</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-crimson text-xl font-medium text-gray-900 mb-2">Have your photo resized correctly</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">US passports require a 2×2 inch (51×51 mm) photo with your head taking up 50–69% of the frame height. Use a passport photo tool to ensure exact sizing.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-tertiary to-green-50 border-2 border-secondary/30 rounded-2xl p-8 text-center">
        <h3 class="font-crimson text-2xl md:text-3xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Create a Perfect Passport Photo Online</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">Use our free passport photo tool to crop and resize any photo to the correct 2×2" dimensions with a white background — accepted by US, India, and 190+ countries.</p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
          <a href="/passport" class="px-6 py-3 bg-gradient-to-br from-primary to-secondary hover:from-secondary hover:to-primary text-white rounded-xl font-crimson font-semibold transition-all duration-300 hover:scale-105 shadow-lg">
            Create Passport Photo
          </a>
          <a href="/blogs" class="px-6 py-3 bg-white hover:bg-gray-50 text-primary border-2 border-primary rounded-xl font-crimson font-semibold transition-all duration-300">
            More Guides
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- Share Section -->
    <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t-2 border-gray-200">
